- Technical experts engaged with Federal Ministry of Health  to support communication, data analysis and public health research)

b) 7 (Q3= 4 Q4 = 3)
(Description: 
- Established a human rights task force with the Federal Ministry of Human Rights to ensure a rights-based approach to relief and recovery efforts from COVID-19. The task force developed a detailed strategy with short, medium and long term targets and recommendations to not only ensure inclusive COVID-19 recovery, but also better preparedness against other disasters in Pakistan
- 5 virtual courts established in Khber Pakhtunkhwa and Merged Areas
- 2 zoom licenses provided  to Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Police, 1 to Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Bar Council and 1 to Peshawar High Court to ensure business continuity. 
- Tehsil Municipal Administrations (TMAs) with the support of Local Government Ambassadors (LGAs) in various districts and tehsil sub-divisions conducted disinfection activities, distributed sanitization supplies and conducted awareness raising sessions.
- Strengthened the capcity of five Depty Commissioner (DC) offices (North Waziristan, South Waziristan, Khyber, Kurram, and Orakzai districts) of Khyber Pakhtunkhwa government through provision of IT and Communication equipment for business continuity.)

